<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n47153b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n47" href="#n47153b">N47 (VI.B.40)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n47all.htm#n47153b"> 153(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> name written on / boat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This Chapter <font color="green">[C]</font> was to recitred over a picture of a boat &hellip; The words and the picture secured for him the entry into the Boat of Ra, and prevented Thoth, who keep a list of all those who entered the boat, from omitting to inscribe his name upon it. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD3"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd Ed (1909) cliv</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Repeated in scribal hand. </mm> </dd></dl>
